function setupLandscapeTokens(scenario)
    local layout = scenario.layout
    if #layout == 2 then
        if #getSeatedPlayers() <= 2 then
            layout = layout[1]
        else
            layout = layout[2]
        end
    end
    local bags = {
        large=getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.bag_large_landscape_token),
        small=getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.bag_small_landscape_token),
    }
    for size, bag in pairs(bags) do
        while scenario[size] < #bag.getObjects() do
            bag.takeObject({callback_function=|o|o.destruct(), position={0,-40,0}})
            waitTime(0.1)
        end
    end
    function passOver(randoms)
        for z=0, 7 do
            local z_fraction = z/7
            local row_min = POSITIONS.landscape_top_left:lerp(POSITIONS.landscape_bottom_left, z_fraction)
            local row_max = POSITIONS.landscape_top_right:lerp(POSITIONS.landscape_bottom_right, z_fraction)
            for x=0, 7 do
                local x_fraction = x/7
                local pos = row_min:lerp(row_max, x_fraction)
                if (layout[z+1][x+1]=="small" or layout[z+1][x+1]=="large") and not randoms then
                    bags[layout[z+1][x+1]].takeObject({position=pos, rotation={0, 180, 0}})
                    waitTime(0.1)
                end
                if layout[z+1][x+1]=="any" and randoms then
                    local number = math.random(2)
                    if number == 1 then
                        if #bags.small.getObjects() > 0 then
                            bags.small.takeObject({position=pos, rotation={0, 180, 0}})
                        else
                            bags.large.takeObject({position=pos, rotation={0, 180, 0}})
                        end
                    elseif number == 2 then
                        if #bags.large.getObjects() > 0 then
                            bags.large.takeObject({position=pos, rotation={0, 180, 0}})
                        else
                            bags.small.takeObject({position=pos, rotation={0, 180, 0}})
                        end
                    end
                    waitTime(0.1)
                end
            end
        end
    end
    passOver()
    passOver(true)
    for _, bag in pairs(bags) do
        bag.destruct()
    end
end

function setupDecorations(scenario)
    local decorations = scenario.decorations
    local decorations_deck = getObjectFromGUID("3dbcb6")
    for _, obj in ipairs(getAllObjects()) do
        local name = obj.getName()
        if decorations[name] ~= nil then
            if decorations[name] then
                if obj.tag == "Deck" then
                    decorations_deck.putObject(obj)
                    waitTime(0.1)
                end
            else
                obj.destruct()
            end
        end
    end
    waitTime(0.5)
    decorations_deck.shuffle()
end

function setupLanterns(scenario)
    local lanterns = scenario.lanterns
    local lantern_bag = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.bag_lanterns)
    local boards = {getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.player_board_red),
                    getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.player_board_yellow),
                    getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.player_board_blue),
                    getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.player_board_green)}

    local i = 1
    for lantern, value in pairs(lanterns) do
        if value then
            function callback(o)
                for _, board in ipairs(boards) do
                    if board ~= nil then
                        local pos = board.positionToWorld(POSITIONS["lantern"..i])
                        local rot = board.getRotation()
                        if scenario.lanterns_flipped then rot.z = rot.z+180 end
                        copy({o})
                        local new = paste({position=pos})
                        new[1].setRotation(rot)
                    end
                end
                o.destruct()
                i = i + 1
            end
            for _, obj in ipairs(lantern_bag.getObjects()) do
                if obj.name == lantern then
                    lantern_bag.takeObject({callback_function=callback, index=obj.index})
                    break
                end
            end
            waitTime(0.5)
        end
    end
    waitTime(1.2)
    if scenario=="solo" then getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS["player_board_red"]).destruct() end
    lantern_bag.destruct()
end

function setupCharacters(scenario)
    local step_size = 1.5
    local x_steps = 6
    local z_steps = 3
    local start = POSITIONS.characters_first
    local zone = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.zone_character_minis)
    local mini_index = {}
    for _, obj in ipairs(zone.getObjects()) do
        mini_index[obj.getName()] = obj
    end
    local script = mini_index.Lady.getLuaScript()
    local character_card_bag = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.bag_character_cards)
    local starting_char_bag = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.bag_starting_chars)
    local starting_char_bag_position = starting_char_bag.getPosition() + Vector(0, 2, 0)
    local characters = scenario.characters
    local start_chars = scenario.start_chars
    for z=0, z_steps do
        for x=0, x_steps do
            local pos = start + Vector({-step_size*x, 0, 0}) + Vector({0, 0, step_size*z})
            local char
            local use = false
            while use==false do
                char, use = next(characters, char)
            end
            if char==nil then break end
            if char=="Herbalist" or char=="Fox Spirit" then
                mini_index[char.." Token"].setPositionSmooth(pos)
                pos.y = pos.y + 2
                waitTime(0.1)
            end
            mini_index[char].setPositionSmooth(pos)
            mini_index[char].setLuaScript(script)
            local card_pos = POSITIONS.character_deck
            local card_rotation = {0.00, 90.00, 180.00}
            if start_chars[char] then
                card_pos = starting_char_bag_position
                card_rotation = {0.00, 90.00, 0}
            end
            for _, obj in ipairs(character_card_bag.getObjects()) do
                if obj.name==char then
                    character_card_bag.takeObject({position=card_pos, rotation=card_rotation, index=obj.index})
                    waitTime(0.1)
                    break
                end
            end
            characters[char] = false
            waitTime(0.1)
        end
    end
    character_card_bag.destruct()
    waitTime(1)
    starting_char_bag.shuffle()
    local color_spots = {
        Red = {{position = {-36.29, 2.53, -20,43}, rotation = {0, 180, 0}}, {position = {-40.29, 2.53, -20,43}, rotation = {0, 180, 0}}},
        Green = {{position = {-36.29, 2.53, 20,43}, rotation = {0, 0, 0}}, {position = {-40.29, 2.53, 20,43}, rotation = {0, 0, 0}}},
        Yellow = {{position = {36.29, 2.53, -20,43}, rotation = {0, 180, 0}}, {position = {40.29, 2.53, -20,43}, rotation = {0, 180, 0}}},
        Blue = {{position = {36.29, 2.53, 20,43}, rotation = {0, 0, 0}},{position = {40.29, 2.53, 20,43}, rotation = {0, 0, 0}}},
    }
    for _, v in ipairs(Player.getPlayers()) do
        if v['color'] != "Black" and v['color'] != "Grey" then
            for q=1, scenario.deal_to_players do
                starting_char_bag.takeObject(color_spots[v['color']][q])
                waitTime(0.2)
            end
        end
    end
    while #starting_char_bag.getObjects() > 0 do
        starting_char_bag.takeObject({position=POSITIONS.character_deck, rotation={0.00, 90.00, 180.00}, smooth=false})
        waitTime(0.1)
    end
    waitTime(0.7)
    starting_char_bag.destruct()
    local deck_zone = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.zone_character_deck)
    local character_deck = nil
    for _, obj in ipairs(deck_zone.getObjects()) do
        if obj.tag == "Deck" then
            character_deck = obj
            break
        end
    end
    character_deck.shuffle()
    waitTime(0.1)
    for q=0, scenario.characters_displayed-1 do
        if character_deck ~= nil then
            character_deck.takeObject({position=POSITIONS.character_deck+Vector(math.floor(q/5)*5.5, 0, ((q%5)*4)+4.5), flip=true})
            waitTime(0.3)
        else
            for _, obj in ipairs(deck_zone.getObjects()) do
                if obj.tag == "Card" then
                    obj.flip()
                    waitTime(0.3)
                end
            end
        end
    end
end

function setupTileDecks(scenario)
    local walled_tiles = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.bag_walled_tao_tiles)
    local palace_bag = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.bag_imperial_palace)
    local decks={
        temples=getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_tao_temples),
        deck_tao = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_tao),
        deck_water = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_water),
        deck_rock = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_rock),
        deck_green = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_green),
        deck_tao_GA = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_golden_age_tao),
        deck_water_GA = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_golden_age_water),
        deck_rock_GA = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_golden_age_rock),
        deck_green_GA = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_golden_age_green),
        deck_tao_GS = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_ghost_stories_tao),
        deck_green_GS = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_ghost_stories_green),
        deck_rock_GS = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_ghost_stories_rock),
        deck_water_GS = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_ghost_stories_water),
        deck_palace_tao = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_ghost_stories_palace_tao),
        deck_palace_water = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_ghost_stories_palace_water),
        deck_palace_green = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_ghost_stories_palace_green),
        deck_palace_rock = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.deck_ghost_stories_palace_rock),
        GA_walled = {},
    }
    for i=1, 3 do
        decks.GA_walled[i] = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS["deck_golden_age_tao_walled_"..i])
    end
    local deck_types = {"tao", "water", "rock", "green"}

    function addWalledToTaoDeck()
        while #walled_tiles.getObjects() > 0 do
            local params = {position=decks.deck_tao.getPosition()+Vector(0, 1, 0), rotation={0,180,180}}
            walled_tiles.takeObject(params)
            waitTime(0.1)
        end
    end

    function addTemplesToTaoDeck()
        while #decks.temples.getObjects() > 0 do
            decks.temples.takeObject({position=decks.deck_tao.getPosition(),  rotation={0, 180, 180}})
            waitTime(0.1)
        end
    end

    function reduceDeckToNumCards(deck, num_cards, market)
        deck.shuffle()
        waitTime(0.1)
        local params = {position={0, 20, 0}, callback_function=|o|o.destruct(), smooth=true}
        if market==true then
            params = {position=POSITIONS.market_deck}
        end
        while #deck.getObjects() > num_cards do
            deck.takeObject(params)
            waitTime(0.1)
        end
    end

    function addSet(set, no_temple)
        if no_temple == true and set=="GS" then
            --don't add the haunted temple
        else
            decks.temples.putObject(decks["deck_tao_"..set])
        end
        if set=="GA"then
            for _, card in ipairs(decks.GA_walled) do
                walled_tiles.putObject(card)
                waitTime(0.1)
            end
        end
        waitTime(0.5)
        for _, type in ipairs(deck_types) do
            if type ~= "tao" then
                decks["deck_"..type].putObject(decks["deck_"..type.."_"..set])
                waitTime(0.1)
            end
        end
    end

    for _, set in ipairs(scenario.tile_sets_to_add) do
        addSet(set, scenario.name=="Haunted Temple")
    end
    waitTime(0.5)
    if scenario.name=="Renovation" then
        walled_tiles.shuffle()
        local wall_placements = {
            {position={-5.61, 1.4, 9.40}, rotate=0},
            {position={5.61, 1.4, 9.40}, rotate=0},
            {position={-9.35, 1.4, 5.64}, rotate=270},
            {position={9.35, 1.4, 5.64}, rotate=90},
            {position={-9.35, 1.4, -5.64}, rotate=270},
            {position={9.35, 1.4, -5.64}, rotate=90},
            {position={-5.61, 1.4, -9.40}, rotate=180},
            {position={5.61, 1.4, -9.40}, rotate=180},
        }
        for _, tile in ipairs(wall_placements) do
            function callback(o)
                local base_rotation = tonumber(o.getDescription())
                local rotation = Vector(0, base_rotation+tile.rotate, 0)
                o.setRotation(rotation)
            end
            walled_tiles.takeObject({position=tile.position, callback_function=callback})
            waitTime(0.2)
        end
    end
    waitTime(0.5)
    addWalledToTaoDeck()
    waitTime(0.5)
    decks.temples.shuffle()
    while #decks.temples.getObjects() > scenario.minimum_number_of_temples do
        decks.temples.takeObject({position=decks.deck_tao.getPosition(), rotation={0, 180, 180}})
        waitTime(0.1)
    end
    waitTime(1)
    for _, type in ipairs(deck_types) do
        local reduce_to = scenario.tile_stack_size
        if type=="tao" then
            reduceDeckToNumCards(decks.deck_tao, reduce_to-scenario.minimum_number_of_temples, scenario.market)
            addTemplesToTaoDeck()
            waitTime(0.5)
        end
        reduceDeckToNumCards(decks["deck_"..type], reduce_to, scenario.market)
    end
    if scenario.name == "Haunted Temple" then
        reduceDeckToNumCards(decks.deck_tao, scenario.tile_stack_size-1, scenario.market)
        decks.deck_tao.putObject(decks.deck_tao_GS)
        waitTime(0.5)
    end
    waitTime(1.5)
    if scenario.market then
        local market_deck = nil
        for _, item in ipairs(getAllObjects()) do
            local item_position = item.getPosition()
            if POSITIONS.market_deck.x-0.01<item_position.x and POSITIONS.market_deck.x+0.01>item_position.x and POSITIONS.market_deck.z-0.01<item_position.z and POSITIONS.market_deck.z+0.01>item_position.z then
                market_deck = item
                break
            end
        end
        market_deck.shuffle()
        waitTime(0.1)
        reduceDeckToNumCards(market_deck, scenario.market_size)
        waitTime(0.3)
        local spacing = market_deck.getBoundsNormalized().size.x
        for i=1, scenario.market_open_tiles do
            params = {position = POSITIONS.market_deck + Vector(spacing*i, 0, 0), flip=true}
            market_deck.takeObject(params)
            waitTime(0.1)
        end
    end
    if scenario.imperial_palace then
        for _, type in ipairs(deck_types) do
            decks["deck_"..type].putObject(decks["deck_palace_"..type])
            waitTime(0.7)
        end
        -- palace_bag.shuffle()
        function callback(o)
            local name = o.getName()
            Wait.condition(||o.lock(), ||o.resting)
            for _, obj in ipairs(getAllObjects()) do
                if obj.getName()==name.." Marker" then
                    obj.setPositionSmooth(o.positionToWorld(POSITIONS.imperial_palace_marker))
                    break
                end
            end
        end
        local variable = math.random(1, 4)
        print("Variable: ", variable)
        for i=1, 4 do
            local params = POSITIONS.imperial_palace[(i+variable)-math.floor((i+variable)/5)*4]
            params.callback_function = callback
            palace_bag.takeObject(params)
            waitTime(0.2)
        end
    end
    walled_tiles.destruct()
    decks.temples.destruct()
    palace_bag.destruct()
    waitTime(1)
    for _, type in ipairs(deck_types) do
        decks["deck_"..type].shuffle()
        waitTime(0.1)
        decks["deck_"..type].takeObject({position = decks["deck_"..type].getPosition()+Vector(0,1,0), flip=true})
        waitTime(0.1)
    end
    waitTime(0.1)
    local central_placement = scenario.central_tile
    local central_tile = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.starting_tile)
    if central_placement=="random" then
        local flipped = math.random(1,2)
        local rotation = math.random(1,4)
        local orientations = {0, 180, 90, 270}
        local set_to = Vector({orientations[flipped], orientations[rotation], 0})
        central_tile.setRotationSmooth(set_to)
    elseif central_placement=="delete" then central_tile.destruct()
    end
    waitTime(0.2)
    if scenario.name=="Uninvited Guests" then
        local cat_location = Vector({ 1.751842, 2.054966, 2.241415 })
        cat_location:rotateOver("y", central_tile.getRotation().y)
        for _, obj in ipairs(getAllObjects()) do
            if obj.getName() == "Uninvited Cat" then
                obj.setPositionSmooth(cat_location)
            end
        end
    end

end

function waitTime(x)
    local time = os.clock()
    while time + x > os.clock() do
        coroutine.yield()
    end
end

function saveToNotes(_, value, id)
    local notes = Notes.getNotebookTabs()
    for _, note in ipairs(notes) do
        if note.title=="Saved Scenario" then
            Notes.removeNotebookTab(note.index)
            break
        end
    end
    Notes.addNotebookTab({
        title = "Saved Scenario",
        body  = JSON.encode_pretty(SCENARIO)
    })
end

function loadFromNotes(_, value, id)
    local notes = Notes.getNotebookTabs()
    for _, note in ipairs(notes) do
        if note.title=="Saved Scenario" then
            SCENARIO = JSON.decode(note.body)
            rebuildUI()
            break
        end
    end
end

function setIn(attr, set, index)
    local flag = false
    local ind = nil
    for i, s in ipairs(SCENARIO[attr]) do
        if s==set then
            flag=true
            ind=i
            break
        end
    end
    if index then
        return flag, ind
    else
        return flag
    end
end

    for _, scen in pairs(SCENARIOS) do

            SCENARIO = scen
            if #SCENARIO.layout == 2 then
                SCENARIO.layout = SCENARIO.layout[2]
            end
            rebuildUI()
        end
    end
end

function toggleLandscape(_, value, id)
    local values={"", "large", "small", "any"}
    local row = tonumber(id:sub(1, 1))
    local col = tonumber(id:sub(2, 2))
    local current = SCENARIO.layout[row][col]
    local next
    for i, x in ipairs(values) do
        if x==current then
            next = (i+1)% (#values+1)
            break
        end
    end
    if next==0 then next=1 end
    SCENARIO.layout[row][col] = values[next]
    rebuildUI()
end

function toggleSet(_, value, id)
    local set = id:sub(-2, -1)
    local attr = id:sub(1,-3)
    local avail, index = setIn(attr, set, true)
    if avail then
        table.remove(SCENARIO[attr], index)
    else
        table.insert(SCENARIO[attr], set)
    end
    rebuildUI()
end

function toggleSelect(_, value, id)
    -- id="includeCharacter" or id="startCharacter"
    local char = ""
    local deco = ""
    local lant = ""
    local start = false
    local include = false
    local decoration = false
    local lantern = true
    if id:sub(1,5)=="start" then
        char = id:sub(6,-1)
        start = true
    elseif id:sub(1,7)=="include" then
        char = id:sub(8,-1)
        include=true
    elseif id:sub(1, 4)=="deco" then
        deco=id:sub(5, -1)
        decoration = true
    elseif id:sub(1,7)=="lantern" then
        lant = id:sub(8,-1)
        lantern=true
    elseif id=="imperial" then
        SCENARIO.imperial_palace = not SCENARIO.imperial_palace
    elseif id=="central_tile" then
        SCENARIO.central_tile = value
    elseif id=="stacksize" then
        SCENARIO.tile_stack_size = tonumber(value)
    elseif id=="minimum_number_of_temples" then
        SCENARIO.minimum_number_of_temples = tonumber(value)
    elseif id=="market" then
        SCENARIO.market = not SCENARIO.market
    elseif id=="market_size" then
        SCENARIO.market_size = tonumber(value)
    elseif id=="market_open_tiles" then
        SCENARIO.market_open_tiles = tonumber(value)
    end


    if start then
        local current = SCENARIO.start_chars[char]
        SCENARIO.start_chars[char] = not SCENARIO.start_chars[char]
        if current==false or current==nil then
            SCENARIO.characters[char] = true
        end
    elseif include then
        local current = SCENARIO.characters[char]
        SCENARIO.characters[char] = not SCENARIO.characters[char]
        if current then
            SCENARIO.start_chars[char] = false
        end
    elseif decoration then
        if deco=="Birds" then
            SCENARIO.decorations.Birds = not SCENARIO.decorations.Birds
            SCENARIO.decorations.Fish = not SCENARIO.decorations.Fish
        elseif deco=="Lotus" then
            SCENARIO.decorations.Lotus = not SCENARIO.decorations.Lotus
            SCENARIO.decorations.Peonies = not SCENARIO.decorations.Peonies
        elseif deco=="Ninfea" then
            SCENARIO.decorations["Sancai Vase"] = not SCENARIO.decorations["Sancai Vase"]
            SCENARIO.decorations["Bonsai Tree"] = not SCENARIO.decorations["Bonsai Tree"]
            SCENARIO.decorations.Ninfea = not SCENARIO.decorations.Ninfea
        else
            SCENARIO.decorations[deco] = not SCENARIO.decorations[deco]
        end
    elseif lantern then
        if lant=="Back" then
            SCENARIO.lanterns_flipped = not SCENARIO.lanterns_flipped
        else
            SCENARIO.lanterns[lant] = not SCENARIO.lanterns[lant]
        end
    end
    rebuildUI()
end

function setupScenario(player, value, id)
    if id and value=="-1" then
        local board = getObjectFromGUID(GUIDS.board)
        board.UI.setAttribute('boxPanel', 'active', 'False')
        board.UI.setAttribute('ScenarioPanel', 'active', 'False')
        board.UI.setAttribute('CraftPanel', 'active', 'False')
        scenario = SCENARIOS[id]
        function scenarioCoroutine()
            setupDecorations(scenario)
            setupTileDecks(scenario)
            setupLandscapeTokens(scenario)
            setupLandscapes(scenario)
            deletePlayerStuffForSolo(scenario)
            setupLanterns(scenario)
            setupCharacters(scenario)
            setMusic()
            return 1
        end
        startLuaCoroutine(self, "scenarioCoroutine")
        local assets = board.UI.getCustomAssets()
        local url
        if id ~= "custom" then
            for _, asset in ipairs(assets) do
                if asset.name == id then
                    url = asset.url
                    break
                end
            end
            local scale = {5, 5, 5}
            if id=="everything" or id=="base_game" then
                scale = {5, 1, 5}
            end
            Global.addDecal({
                name             = id,
                url              = url,
                position         = Vector(-30, 1, 0),
                rotation         = Vector(90, 270, 0),
                scale            = scale,
            })
        end
        loadStats(self.script_state, "https://script.google.com/macros/s/AKfycbyxgFb6niiidCGxELlCqN4cu0sbulPTi6aOjfgG/exec", 600, 120, false)
        LOADED = true
        current_save = JSON.decode(self.script_state)
        if not current_save then current_save={} end
        current_save.LOADED = LOADED
        self.script_state = JSON.encode(current_save)
    end
end

STAT_URL = ""
ID = false
DEBUG = false


function start_tracker()
  loadStats(initial_wait, interval, debug)
end

function loadStats(initial_wait, interval, debug)
    local initial_wait = initial_wait or 600
    local interval = interval or 120
    if debug then DEBUG=debug end

    local state = JSON.decode(self.script_state)
    if state and state ~= "" then
        if DEBUG then log("Found save state") end
        if state.ID then
            if DEBUG then log("found ID "..state.ID.." in save state") end
            ID = state.ID
        else
            if DEBUG then log("no ID found in save_state. Registering new session") end
        end
    end
    if not ID then
        if DEBUG then log("No ID so setting timer to request new one.") end
        function get_id()
            WebRequest.post(STAT_URL, {moment="start", num_players=#getSeatedPlayers(), delay=initial_wait}, save_id)
        end
        Wait.time(get_id, initial_wait)
        Wait.time(ping, interval, -1)
    else
        if DEBUG then log("Session already started (rewinded?) only setting interval") end
        Wait.time(ping, interval, -1)
    end
end

function l(w)
    if DEBUG then log(w.text) end
end

function ping()
    if DEBUG then log("Pinging stats.") end
    WebRequest.post(STAT_URL, {moment="ping", id=ID, num_players=#getSeatedPlayers()}, l)
end

function save_id(w)
    if DEBUG then log("Received ID.") end
    if DEBUG then log(w.text) end
    current_save = JSON.decode(self.script_state)
    if not current_save then current_save={} end
    ret = JSON.decode(w.text)
    ID = ret.id
    current_save["ID"] = ID
    if DEBUG then log(current_save) end
    self.script_state = JSON.encode(current_save)
end

function onSave()
    return self.script_state
end

--Counting Tile    modified from MrStump's Counting Bowl

--Table of items which can be counted in this Tile
--Each entry has 2 things to enter
    --a name (what is in the name field of that object)
    --a value (how much it is worth)
--A number in the items description will override the number entry in this table
validCountItemList = {
     ["1 point"] = 1,
     ["5 points"] = 5,
     ["10 points"] = 10,
     ["20 points"] = 20,
    --Add more entries as needed
    --Remove the -- from before a line for the script to use it
}

--END OF CODE TO EDIT

function onLoad()
    --Sets position/color for the button, spawns it
    self.createButton({
        label="", click_function="none", function_owner=self,
        position={-2.55,0.12,0.7}, rotation={0,0,0}, height=00, width=0,
        font_color={255,255,255}, font_size=250
    })
    --Start timer which repeats forever, running countItems() every second
    timerID = self.getGUID()..math.random(9999999999999)
    Timer.create({
        identifier=timerID,
        function_name="countItems", function_owner=self,
        repetitions=0, delay=1
    })
end

--Activated once per second, counts items in bowls
function countItems()
    local totalValue = 0
    local itemsInBowl = findItemsInBox()
    --Go through all items found by the cast
    for _, entry in ipairs(itemsInBowl) do
        --Ignore the bowl
        if entry.hit_object ~= self then
            local tableEntry = validCountItemList[entry.hit_object.getName()]
            --Ignore if not in validCountItemList
            if tableEntry ~= nil then
                local descValue = tonumber(entry.hit_object.getDescription())
                local stackMult = math.abs(entry.hit_object.getQuantity())
                --Use value in description if available
                if descValue ~= nil then
                    totalValue = totalValue + descValue * stackMult
                else
                    --Otherwise use the value in validCountItemList
                    totalValue = totalValue + tableEntry * stackMult
                end
            end
        end
    end
    --Updates the number display
    self.editButton({index=0, label=totalValue})
end

--Gets the items in the box for countItems to count
function findItemsInBox()
    --Find scaling factor
    local scale = self.getScale()
    --Set position for the box
    local pos = self.getPosition()
    pos.y=pos.y+1.25
    --Ray trace to get all objects
    return Physics.cast({
        origin=pos, direction={0,1,0}, type=3, max_distance=0,
        size={4.9*scale.x,3.4*scale.y,0.9*scale.z}, --debug=true
    })
end

function onDestroy()
    t = Timer.destroy(timerID)
end

    local player = Player[player_color]
    local distance = 3
    if player.getHoverObject() == self then
        local pos_target = self.getTransformForward()
        local pos_current = self.getPosition()
        local pos = {
            x = pos_current.x + pos_target.x * distance,
            y = pos_current.y + pos_target.y * distance,
            z = pos_current.z + pos_target.z * distance,
        }
        local rot = self.getRotation()[2]
        local params = {
            position = pos,
            distance = 1,
            yaw = 360 - (0-rot),
            pitch = 30
            }
        player.lookAt(params)
    end    
end

0.title: Custom Scenarios
0.body:
You can store and save a custom scenario to the notebook tab. 

By clicking the "Save to Notes" button a notebook tab named: "Saved Scenario" will be created/overwritten.

When clicking the "Load from Notes" button it will look for, and load a scenario from a notebook tab with that name.
